                    <msContents>
                        <summary>A Persian commentary by Khalīl Ibn al-Ghāzī al-Qazvīnī of
                                <title>Kitāb al-ṣalawāt</title><title xml:lang="per">کتاب الصلوةکتاب
                                الصلوة</title> the eleventh book of the great work on religious law
                            of the Shi’ite traditions <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Usūl
                                al-Kāfī</title><title xml:lang="ara">اصول الكافي</title>، by <name
                                key="n80158377" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/60393215/"><persName
                                    xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Kulaynī, Muḥammad ibn
                                    Yaʻqūb, d. 941?</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara">كليني، محمد بن يعقوب</persName></name>.
                            Al-Kāfī, writen originally in Arabic, contains some 80 thousand
                            traditions, divided into 33 books (for the titles see Ethe, 2667, p.
                            1451). The present Persian commentary, a response to the royal command,
                            as stated in the preface, was commenced in the month of Rajab the year
                                <date calendar="Hijri-qamari" when="1659">1070</date><foreign
                                xml:lang="per">شروع شد در شرح کتاب یازدهم است بتاریخ رجب سال هزار و
                                هفتاد هجری </foreign>, by then the commentator had already completed
                            the first ten books of the Al-Kāfī the titles of which are given in the
                            preface <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus>
                            <foreign xml:lang="per">کتاب العقل و کتاب التوحید و کتاب الحجه و کتاب
                                الحجه و کتاب الایمان و الکفر و کتاب الدعا و کتاب فضل القرآن و کتاب
                                العشرة و کتاب الجنایز</foreign> and at the end of this work he
                            states that it would be followed by Kitāb al-Zakāt <foreign
                                xml:lang="per">این آخر کتاب الصلوة است از کتاب کافی از ابو جعفر
                                کلینی... و در عقب آن می آید کتاب الزکوة قدوفق الشارح خلیل بن الغازی
                                القزوینی...</foreign> The Persian commentary is divided into one
                            hundred and three bāb <foreign xml:lang="per">باب</foreign></summary>
